headline: Target Stock Looks Cheap but It May Be a Bargain Today for a Much Better Reason
summary: Target's stock has dropped to cheap levels because of slumping sales and worries over higher costs.  Investors could be under-appreciating this one opportunity that's already boosting profits for Target's top peers in the retail space.  Well-know retailer Target (NYSE: TGT) trades at just 11 times its earnings, which is about 60% cheaper than the S&P 500, which trades at about 28 times earnings, according to YCharts.
